docs.abstract: A new standard, called Stir/Shaken, could come to your mobile provider by the end of the year. But there are already ways around it.
docs.snippet: A new standard, called Stir/Shaken, could come to your mobile provider by the end of the year. But there are already ways around it.
docs.lead_paragraph: Anthony Marino set his mobile phone to “Do Not Disturb” before going to bed, but he sensed it flicker in the dark. The next morning, he saw he had missed roughly 30 calls: at 4:15 a.m., 4:34, 4:45, 5:08 and 5:12, and for two hours after that. Most appeared as “Lithuania” on his caller ID, although they could have come from anywhere.

headline.main: Phone Companies Are Testing Tech to Catch Spam Calls. Let’s Hope It Works.
